HLC Homework 2: Plotting

To check your understanding of ggplot and topics covered in todays lesson, replicate the plot below of data from the Gapminder dataset to the best of your ability. Make use of your resources the HLC Day2 R markdown document, the ggplot2 documentation, R for Data Science, and Google. Create a new R script or R markdown document of your to run the code for your answer.

First, load the gapminder and ggplot libraries into R

library(gapminder)
library(ggplot2)

This plot uses the following subset of the Gapminder data:

finalExampleData <- dplyr::filter(gapminder, year %in% c(1952, 2007))

Hints:

This plot has:

  • Facets to show the different years. Try looking at the help page for facet_wrap.
  • A linear trendline
  • A log10 scale x-axis
  • Altered transparency of the points
  • Renamed legend titles
  • Axis text resized to 12
  • Axis title text resized to 14
  • Facet titles resized to 14
